@Node "FreeDB_Introduction" "Introduction"

  @{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}


    In the following the term:

    - @{fg shine}freedb@{fg text} is used to indicate the @{fg shine}freedb protocol@{fg text}
      as defined at @{fg shine}http//www.freedb.org@{fg text}

    - @{fg shine}FreeDB@{fg text} is used to indicate the @{fg shine}freedb Amiga package@{fg text}

    - @{fg shine}FreeDB@{fg text} is also used to indicate the@{fg shine} main FreeDB Application@{fg text}


    @{fg shine}FreeDB@{fg text} is the package to use the freedb protocol on Amiga.

    @{fg shine}freedb@{fg text} (http://www.freedb.org) is a protocol that defines a
    set of rules to store and to retrieve (locally and remotly)
    CDROM information.

    The topic to handle with CDROM is the @{fg shine}DiscID@{fg text}.

    The @{fg shine}DiscID@{fg text} is an integral number, rappresented as a 8 digits
    hex number. The DiscID is computed on the @{fg shine}Table Of
    Contents@{fg text} (TOC) of a CDROM. The TOC contains various
    information about the CDROM such as the number of the tracks
    and the start position and the duration of each track and. It
    seems immediately clear that different CDROMs may have the
    same DiscID. It means that we need another peace of
    information to identify a CDROM in an unique way.

    freedb protocol introduces the Category (Categ) of a CDROM:
    CDROMs in the same Categ have different DiscID. It means that
    the couple <Categ,DiscID> may rappresent just a single CDROM.

    Information are stored as text files. These files are named
    as the DiscID and they resides in directories, which are
    named as the Categs:

    root drawer
    +--misc
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--blues
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--classical
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--country
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--data
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--folk
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--jazz
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--newage
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--reggae
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--rock
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN
    +--soundtrack
       +--DiscID1
       +--DiscID2
       +--...
       \--DiscIDN

    As you can see, the Categs are
    - misc
    - blues
    - classical
    - country
    - data
    - folk
    - jazz
    - newage
    - reggae
    - rock
    - soundtrack

    They are subdirectories of the "Root Drawer".

@EndNode

@Node "FreeDB_App" "FreeDB"

  @{u}@{b}FreeDB@{ub}@{uu}


    FreeDB is the main application.

    It lets you retrieve and modify discs information.

    The application has 2 main pages:

    - @{"Edit" LINK "FreeDB_Edit"} page
      Made of 4 pages where to edit the discs data. In the first
      page, double clicking on a track in the tracks list, starts
      playing from that track.

    - Multi matches page
      When multi matches are found locally or on a freedb server,
      you may double click on an entry to choose that.

    FreeDB also offers also an ARexx port.

    It accepts the following commands:

    - @{fg shine}BREAK@{fg text}
      Breaks active connection

    - @{fg shine}GETDISC@{fg text} LOCAL/S,REMOTE/S
      Tries to obtain disc information. The LOCAL switch forces
      to search only in the local database. The REMOTE switch
      forces to ignore the local database.

    - @{fg shine}PLAY@{fg text} STOP/S,ALL/S,LIST/S,NEXT/S
      Controls playing.

    - @{fg shine}SUBMIT@{fg text}

    - @{fg shine}GETINFO@{fg text} STEM/A
      Writes disc information in stem.

      The following fields are set:

        - DI
          BOOLEAN
          0 if freedb disc info are not available, 1 otherwise

        - TOC
          BOOLEAN
          0 if disc info are not available, 1 otherwise

        If both di and toc are 0 you got nothing (e,g. error or
        no disc inserted).

        - DISCID
          STRING
          The freedb DiscID of the disc

        - TRACKS
          NUMERIC
          The number of the tracks

        - NUM
          NUMERIC
          As TRACKS

        - FIRST
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          The first track

        - LAST
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          The last track

        - STARTADDR
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Disc frame start addr

        - ENDADDR
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Disc frame end addr

        - FRAMES
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Disc total frames

        - MIN
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Disc minutes length

        - SEC
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Disc seconds length

        - FRAME
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Disc frames length

        - DATA
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - BOOLEAN
          0 if the disc contains no data track, 1 otherwise

        - AUDIO
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - BOOLEAN
          0 if the disc contains no audio track, 1 otherwise

        - CATEG
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          freedb category

        - TITLE
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          Disc title

        - ARTIST
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          Disc artist

        - GENRE
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          Musical disc genre

        - YEAR
          Only valid if DI is 1 - NUMERIC

        - MULTIARTIST
          Only valid if DI is 1 - BOOLEAN
          1 if the disc is a compilation, 0 otherwise

        - EXTD
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          Disc extended info

        - PLAYORDER
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING

        Then for i=0,...,tracks-1

        - i.TRACK
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i track number

        - i.STARTADDR
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i start address

        - i.ENDADDR
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i end address

        - i.FRAMES
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i total frames

        - i.STARTMIN
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i start min

        - i.STARTSEC
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i start sec

        - i.STARTFRAME
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i start rame

        - i.ENDMIN
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i end min

        - i.ENDSEC
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i end sec

        - i.ENDFRAME
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i end frame

        - i.MIN
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i total min

        - i.SEC
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i total sec

        - i.FRAME
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - NUMERIC
          Track i total frames

        - i.AUDIO
          Only valid if TOC is 1 - BOOLEAN
          0 if track i is a data track, 1 otherwise

        - i.SEL
          BOOLEAN
          1 if track i is selected in FreeDB, 0 otherwise

        - i.TITLE
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          Track i title

        - i.ARTIST
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          Track i artist (Set iff MULTIARTIST is 1)

        - i.EXTD
          Only valid if DI is 1 - STRING
          Track i extended info


        Example:

        /* Show selected tracks info */
        options results

        "GETINFO" di
        if ~di.di | ~di.toc | ~di.audio then exit

        ma=di.multiartist

        do i=0 to di.tracks-1

            if ~di.i.sel | ~di.i.audio then iterate

            tn=right("00" || di.i.track,2)
            if ma then a=di.artist
            else a=di.i.artist

            say tn "TITLE " di.i.title
            say tn "ARTIST" a
            say tn "AUDIO " di.i.audio
            say
        end

@EndNode

@Node "FreeDB_Applications" "Applications"

  @{u}@{b}Applications@{ub}@{uu}


    FreeDB consists of:

    - @{"freedb.library" LINK "FreeDB_Introduction"}
      This is a shared AmigaDOS Library that offers a complete
      api to the freedb protocol. It doesn't include any GUI
      function itself but it uses external GUI engines mechanism.

    - @{"FreeDB" LINK "FreeDB_App"}
      This is the main FreeDB application. It handles disc
      informations.

    - @{"GetDisc" LINK "FreeDB_GDDisc"}
      It is called from applications that needs to find disc
      information.

    - @{"Discs manager" LINK "FreeDB_DiscsManager"}
      Manages discs information

@EndNode

@Node "FreeDB_AppPrefs" "FreeDB preferences"

  @{u}@{b}FreeDB preferences@{ub}@{uu}


    - Buttons
      The appearance of the buttons. Note that many other settings
      are available in MUI Settings/TheBar

    - Options

      . Bold list title
        If selected the lists titles are drawn bold

      . No bar among columns
        If selected bars among lists columns are not drawn

      . Hide bar
        If selected the bar is hidden.

@EndNode
@Node "FreeDB_AppMenus" "FreeDB menus"

  @{u}@{b}FreeDB menus@{ub}@{uu}


    - Project

      . About
        Opens the about window

      . AboutMUI
        Opens the about MUI window

      . Hide
        Iconifies FreeDB

      . Quit
        Quits FreeDB

      . Stop and Quit
        Stops playing and quits FreeDB

    - FreeDB

      . Search
        Starts looking up a disc

      . Search local
        Starts looking up a disc only in the local cache

      . Search remote
        Starts looking up a disc only on the freedb server

      . Save
        Saves data to the local cache.

      . Submit
        Sends data to the freedb server.

      . Stop
        Breaks active connection.

      . Disc
        Moves to the data page.

      . Case conversion
        Converts all first letters to uppercase.

      . Matches
        Moves to multi matches page.

      . Configuration
        Opens the freedb.library configuration window

      . Discs manager
        Launches Discs manager application

      . Execute macro
        Launches a macro

    - Player

      . Playlist
        Starts playing tracks as defined in the playlist.

      . Play next
        Plays next track in the playlist.

      . Stop playing
        Stops play operation.

      . Toggle pause
        Toggles pause if playing.

      . Toggle door
        Opens/Closes CD drive door.


    - Settings

      . Edit
        Opens the preferences window.

      . Save
        Saves preferences.

      . Last saved
        Restore last saved preferences.

      . Reset to defaults
        Set preferences to default values.

      . MUI Settings
        Opens the MUI settings window

@EndNode

@Node "FreeDB_Config" "Configuration"

  @{u}@{b}Configuration@{ub}@{uu}


    Here you may edit and modify the freedb.library configuration
    stored in FreeDB:Default.FreeDB:

    - Local

      . Root
        The location of your local cache.


    - Remote
      List of freedb sites. If no sites is defined or no site is
      defined are the Active one, the one and only static default
      site "freedb.freedb.org" is used

     . User

       o User
         Your nick name. Default "ILoveNeYork"

       o EMail
         Your EMail addr. Needed to send information to a freedb
         server. No default

     . Proxy

       o Proxy
         The name of a proxy to use. No default

       o Port
         The port for the proxy. Default 8080

       o Use
         Use the proxy. Default NO

    - GUI
      The Gui engine to use.

@EndNode

@Node "FreeDB_ConfigMenus" "Configuration menus"

  @{u}@{b}Configuration menus@{ub}@{uu}


    - Project

      . Restore
        Restore the configuration from FreeDB:Default.FreeDB

      . Save
        Save the configuration in FreeDB:Default.FreeDB

      . Get sites
        Clears sites list and downloads sites from a freedb
        server.

      . Add sites
        Downloads sites from a freedb server.

      . Close
        Closes freedb.library configuration window

@EndNode

